@startuml component-tab-dual-representation
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because this shows ONE ordered model feeding TWO views through a shared component,
'' with the reorder flowing back to mutate the single source — a component picture with bidirectional,
'' concept-coloured wiring that Mermaid's flowchart cannot colour per concept as cleanly.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Tabs — one ordered model, two representations (reordering either reorders both)

rectangle "app-db [:ui :tabs]\nORDERED vector of tabs\n(the single source of truth)" as MODEL APPDB_TINT

rectangle "vinary.ui.tabs/tab-item\nshared component\n(click · × close · right-click menu · draggable)" as ITEM RENDERER_TINT

rectangle "horizontal tab strip\n(above the content pane)\nleft → right" as STRIP RENDERER_TINT
rectangle "vertical Tabs sidebar panel\n(Files · Contents · Tabs)\ntop → bottom" as PANEL RENDERER_TINT

rectangle ":tab/reorder\n(reg-event-db → nav/reorder)\nvector splice" as REORDER REFRAME_TINT
rectangle ":context-menu/show {:kind :tab}\nClose · Close Others ·\nClose to the Right · View Source" as CTX REFRAME_TINT

MODEL --> STRIP : render in :order
MODEL --> PANEL : render in the SAME :order
STRIP --> ITEM  : each tab
PANEL --> ITEM  : each tab
ITEM  --> REORDER : drag-drop (x-midpoint on the strip, y-midpoint in the panel)
ITEM  --> CTX     : right-click
REORDER --> MODEL : splice [:ui :tabs] → both views re-render

note bottom #FFF6D6
  Because both representations render the **same** ordered `[:ui :tabs]` vector through the **same**
  `tab-item`, top→bottom in the panel always equals left→right in the strip, and a drag in either one
  splices the one vector — so the orders never drift. The vertical panel is most useful when more tabs are
  open than fit horizontally.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db ordered tab model [:ui :tabs] |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| renderer views + the shared tab-item |
  |<#4F97D7>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| re-frame events (reorder, context menu) |
endlegend
@enduml
